## Technical Considerations

### Architecture
- `_bindings.py` becomes the single source of truth for shared bindings — widgets import from it
- The `HelpScreen` needs to collect bindings from multiple widgets. It can use `self.app.screen.active_bindings` for the current context, or iterate over known widget classes' `BINDINGS` for a complete view
- Binding `group` parameter controls how the Footer groups keys visually

### Textual Version Compatibility
- Perch uses Textual **1.1** — `group`, `tooltip`, `id` on Binding are available (added in 0.63+)
- `Footer(compact=True)` is available (added in 0.63+)
- `ModalScreen` for help screen is available

### Performance
- No performance impact — binding resolution is already O(widget-chain-depth) per key press
- Help screen renders once on open; no continuous computation

### Risks
- **Footer rendering with groups**: Need to verify how Textual 1.1 renders grouped bindings in compact mode — may need CSS tweaks
- **`check_action` interactions**: Viewer's existing `check_action` must still work correctly after binding reorganization

## Success Criteria

### Automated Verification
- [ ] `make test` passes with all new and updated tests
- [ ] `make lint` passes
- [ ] `make typecheck` passes
- [ ] No DRY violations in binding definitions (each shared binding defined exactly once)

### Manual Verification
- [ ] Focus FileTree → footer shows: Refresh, Open, Search, Navigate, Help (~5 items)
- [ ] Focus Viewer → footer shows: Diff, Layout, Markdown (conditional), Scroll, Help
- [ ] Focus GitPanel → footer shows: Refresh, Select, Navigate, Help
- [ ] Focus GitHubPanel → footer shows: Open, Refresh, Navigate, Help
- [ ] Press `?` → help screen opens with all bindings grouped by context
- [ ] Press `Escape` on help screen → returns to app
- [ ] Press `Ctrl+Shift+P` → command palette opens (unchanged)
- [ ] Footer is visually compact and readable

## Dependencies & Risks

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|------------|
| Textual Footer `group` rendering may not match Lazygit aesthetic | Test early in Phase 2; fall back to CSS customization or custom Footer subclass if needed |
| Rebinding `?` may break muscle memory for command palette users | Command palette still available via `Ctrl+Shift+P`; document in README |
| `active_bindings` API may not expose all widget bindings for help screen | Fall back to iterating known widget class BINDINGS directly |

## Open Questions

| Question | Options | Source |
|----------|---------|--------|
| Should help screen show ALL bindings or only bindings for current context? | A: All (like Lazygit `?`), B: Current context only | Design decision — Lazygit shows all organized by panel |
| Should `?` toggle the help screen or always push? | A: Toggle (press again to close), B: Push (Escape to close) | UX preference |
| Should we add `tooltip` text to footer hover or just use it in help screen? | A: Both, B: Help screen only | Depends on terminal hover support |

